description.de:
Die Schulfach Ontologie ist ein formales Modell zur Definition und Organisation der Schulfächer in den deutschen Bundesländern. Sie stellt ein strukturiertes Vokabular bereit, um Schulfächer und deren Beziehungen zu beschreiben, zu klassifizieren und zu verknüpfen – und ermöglicht dadurch die Interoperabilität von Bildungsdaten über verschiedene Systeme und Institutionen hinweg.
GitHub: https://fwu-de.github.io/schulfach-ontologie/
description.en:
The German school subjects ontology is a formal semantic model that defines and organizes the school subjects (Schulfächer) used across the German federal states (Bundesländer). It provides a structured vocabulary for describing, categorizing, and interlinking school subjects and their relationships—allowing data interoperability across different educational datasets and systems. 
GitHub: https://fwu-de.github.io/schulfach-ontologie/

comment.de:
Ein “Schulfach” ist eine “Informationseinheit”.
Es handelt sich um die Bezeichnung eines an der Schule unterrichteten Fachs. 
Es ist der Ausdruck für die thematische Gliederung dessen, was jeweils unter allgemeiner schulischer Bildung verstanden wird. 
Das Schulfach ist ein Themengebiet, das den Unterricht inhaltlich unterteilt. Beispiele für Schulfächer sind Deutsch, Mathematik, Geschichte und Biologie.
comment.en:
A "Schulfach" is an “information content entity”.
It refers to the designation of a subject taught at school.
It represents the thematic structure of what is considered general school education.
A "Schulfach" is a subject area that organizes teaching lessons by content.
Examples of "Schulfächer" include German, mathematics, history, and biology.

definition.value: skos:closeMatch is used to link two concepts that are sufficiently similar that they can be used interchangeably in some information retrieval applications. In order to avoid the possibility of "compound errors" when combining mappings across more than two concept schemes, skos:closeMatch is not declared to be a transitive property.
Relates, by convention, a concept scheme to a concept which is topmost in the broader/narrower concept hierarchies for that scheme, providing an entry point to these hierarchies.

skos:exactMatch is used to link two concepts, indicating a high degree of confidence that the concepts can be used interchangeably across a wide range of information retrieval applications. skos:exactMatch is a transitive property, and is a sub-property of skos:closeMatch.
Relates a concept to the concept scheme that it is a top level concept of.
